    <!-- Application Structure Plan: 
         1. Hero Section: Immediate value proposition and professional identity.
         2. Skills Dashboard: Quantitative visualization of expertise (Radar Chart) to establish authority.
         3. Interactive Portfolio Matrix: The core section. Instead of a linear list, a filterable grid where users can "drill down" into case studies. 
            Interaction involves expanding cards to reveal "Before/After" micro-interactions derived directly from the source manuals (e.g., URL optimization, Error messages).
         4. Process Visualization: A timeline/flow showing the methodology (Research -> Structure -> Content -> Validation).
         5. Footer: Contact info.
         Why: This structure proves the "UX Content" skill by organizing complex portfolio data into a digestible, hierarchical interactive experience.
    -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         - Skill Radar (Chart.js): To visualize the multi-disciplinary nature (Design + Content + SEO).
         - Interactive "Content Fixer": JS-driven text toggles to demonstrate UX Writing impact (Bad Copy vs Good Copy) based on the "Gu√≠a de contenido" and "Manuals".
         - Bar Chart (Chart.js): To show the distribution of work across different industries/clients.
         - Logic: NO SVG used. All icons are unicode or CSS shapes. Charts are Canvas.
    -->
